news.title: China: Court auction to sell Shimao Group's land in Shenzhen fails again
news.para: Twelve land plots totalling 243,602 square metres, together with some uncompleted buildings on them, have asked for 10.4 billion yuan ($1.4 billion), 20% lower than the 13 billion yuan starting price in the first auction in July, according to e-commerce company JD.com's online auction platform.

news.title: Canadian home sales post biggest decline in 16 months in October
news.para: Canadian home sales fell 5.6% in October from September, the fourth straight month of declines and the biggest since June 2022. On an annual basis, without adjustment for seasonal variation, sales were up 0.9%.

news.title: Suraksha Realty directors buy Rs 100-crore apartments in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: The brothers have purchased the apartments on the top floors of the super luxury project Naman Xena. Each of these apartments are spread over 6,458 sq ft of carpet area on the 26th and 27th floors of the under-construction tower.

news.title: Six months on, PWD's smart streetlight project yet to start in Delhi
news.para: The policy was approved in June by chief minister Arvind Kejriwal, with an aim to reduce electricity consumption and find a way to fix the problems with the conventional high-pressure sodium lights.

news.title: Religare Housing Finance looks to touch Rs 70-80 crore disbursal in FY24
news.para: Religare Housing Finance's book size is around Rs 255 crore net non-performing assets (NPA) is around 2.3 per cent and borrowing cost is in excess of around 12 per cent.

news.title: Kochi metro not to wait for decision on land acquisition
news.para: KMRL is planning to start the construction works of the other eight stations if the process of acquiring the land for Chembumukku and Padamugal stations are delayed.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body issues notices to 190 constructions sites
news.para: According to Chayya Dangale, public relation officer of Ulhasnagar Municipal Corporation, civic officials issued notices to 190 construction sites, reiterating the guidelines of the latest mitigation plans.

news.title: Kochi: Housing complex project to be ready by February 2024
news.para: The first housing complex is being constructed at Thuruthy. Kochi corporation is implementing the project with the financial support of Cochin Smart Mission Ltd (CSML).

news.title: Chandigarh administration plans new government housing, starts survey
news.para: In a first step, it has started a ground survey of all government housing to identify, among other things, demand-supply gap in different categories.

news.title: Construction activities rampant in Gurugram despite curbs
news.para: Despite enforcement teams in action and issuing of challans, Haryana Shahri Vikas Parishad (HSVP) and MCG have failed to check construction activities completely making mockery of ban imposed as per GRAP norms.

news.title: Credai wants CAQM to lift construction ban in NCR
news.para: Manoj Gaur, the president of the real estate developers’ body, highlighted that for three days after Diwali air quality in NCR was below 400 (very poor). Since Monday, the AQIs in Noida, Greater Noida and Ghaziabad were between 320 and 375.

news.title: Puravankara acquires rights for three-acre redevelopment project in Mumbai
news.para: Puravankara's project has a cumulative estimated development potential of 5.8 lakh sq ft carpet area, with approximately 3.65 lakh sq ft available for sale and a potential gross development value (GDV) of Rs 1,500 crore.

news.title: Control of Aamby Valley stays with the Sahara Group
news.para: Aamby Valley, spread across more than 10,000 acres in western Maharashtra, is a premium gated city with luxury villas, an 18-hole Golf course, and over 90% of landscaped open spaces.

news.title: Telangana RERA slaps notices on builders for violations
news.para: Notices were slapped on Neemsboro group, Excellence Properties, Prestige Group projects, Urban Yards, Happy Dream homes, Seven Hills, Kavuri Hills, Rivendell Farms, Sumadhura Infra Projects and other companies for advertising their projects and pre-launches without RERA registration.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC draws flak for nod to 10,000 PAP flats on private plot in three days
news.para: ​It also allowed the new landowner, a Pune-based company, to develop the vacant plot under the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) scheme to get more floor space index (FSI) for construction.

news.title: Mumbai: Royal Realtors' partner who cheated buyers of Rs 11 crore gets three years' jail
news.para: The main complainant in the case, a mother-son duo had bought a 1,000 sq ft flat in the building for Rs 57 lakh and paid the full amount in 2012.

news.title: China's property sales extend declines, weighing on outlook
news.para: Property sales by floor area fell 20.33% year-on-year against a 19.77% fall in September, according to Reuters calculations based on data released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Boston Properties to sell interest in two assets valued at about $1.7 billion
news.para: Massachusetts, especially Cambridge and Boston, is known to be a hotspot for biotech companies including Moderna. The state is also regarded as the top biopharma cluster in the United States.

news.title: China land sales revenue falls at faster pace, squeezing local governments
news.para: Revenue from land sales fell 25.4% in October from a year earlier, extending a decline of 21.3% the prior month, according to Reuters calculations based on data from the finance ministry.

news.title: Odisha cabinet gives green signal to Rs 5,929 crore Bhubaneswar metro project
news.para: T​​he Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) will execute the Rs 5,929.38 crore project as a turn-key consultant by charging a fee of Rs 326.56 crore.
